    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-30T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-30T14:00:00-05:00" n="254"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d254">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 657.119/269a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Norway</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SAG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schmedeman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-30T14:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 30, 1918—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>218. The following additions have been made to the proposed schedule of
                    commodities to be furnished the Norwegian Government, cabled you January 19:
                    After “fruit, fresh” insert “sugar, 50,000; pork and beef, 10,000.” After
                    “mineral oils” insert “oil seeds (for seed crushing plants), 20,000.” Insert
                    following paragraph after sentence ending “her own production of foodstuffs “:
                    “Subject to restrictions and considerations set forth in our letter of December
                    19 Norway is to receive, in so far as our own needs will permit and subject to
                    the necessary allotments to the countries associated with us in the war and
                    supplies to other neutral countries, the following commodities in quantities to
                    be determined by her needs to be hereafter ascertained: metals, machinery of all
                    kinds, fixtures, motor cars, motor trucks, bicycles, writing machines, cash
                    registers, accounting machines, hardware and tools, chemicals, dyes, colors,
                    drugs, medicines, resin, tobacco, tanning extracts, shoes and rubbers.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
